                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163P92/100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gourley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-26T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 26, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 26—9:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My May 25, 2 p.m., and May 25, 8 p.m.<note n="26" xml:id="d436fn26">Neither
                        printed; see Department’s reply, May 25, 9 p.m., <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra.</hi>
                    </note> American Presbyterian Mission in Tsingtao ordered all refugees to leave
                    school compound and notified Japanese that order had been given. Relatives of
                    suspected man have already left.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow, Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gourley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
